 very use of such tests to identify an athlete's sex and/or gender are highly problematic.\", \"from\": 3112, \"to\": 3214, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 3115, \"to\": 3119}, {\"ngram\": \"the very use\", \"from\": 3121, \"to\": 3133}, {\"ngram\": \"such tests\", \"from\": 3137, \"to\": 3147}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete's sex and/or gender\", \"from\": 3160, \"to\": 3190}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since 1968, some sportswomen competing in the Olympics have had to undergo humiliatingtests \\\"proving\\\" their gender identities.\", \"from\": 3216, \"to\": 3342, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some sportswomen\", \"from\": 3228, \"to\": 3244}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3258, \"to\": 3270}, {\"ngram\": \"humiliatingtests\", \"from\": 3291, \"to\": 3307}, {\"ngram\": \"their gender identities\", \"from\": 3318, \"to\": 3341}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This often involved visual examinations of their genitals in front of doctors and other medical experts.\", \"from\": 3343, \"to\": 3447, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This often involved visual examinations\", \"from\": 3343, \"to\": 3382}, {\"ngram\": \"their genitals\", \"from\": 3386, \"to\": 3400}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 3404, \"to\": 3409}, {\"ngram\": \"doctors\", \"from\": 3413, \"to\": 3420}, {\"ngram\": \"other medical experts\", \"from\": 3425, \"to\": 3446}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mandated by the IOC, \\\"gender verification\\\" tests were then implemented by international sports organisations.\", \"from\": 3449, \"to\": 3558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3465, \"end\": 3468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3098228103452494e-42, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gender verification\\\" tests\", \"from\": 3471, \"to\": 3497}, {\"ngram\": \"international sports organisations\", \"from\": 3523, \"to\": 3557}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Underpinning such practices was a set ofproblematic assumptions, particularly that a woman who is good at sport could perhaps be a man masquerading as female.\", \"from\": 3560, \"to\": 3718, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such practices\", \"from\": 3573, \"to\": 3587}, {\"ngram\": \"a set ofproblematic assumptions\", \"from\": 3592, \"to\": 3623}, {\"ngram\": \"a woman\", \"from\": 3643, \"to\": 3650}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 3666, \"to\": 3671}, {\"ngram\": \"a man\", \"from\": 3689, \"to\": 3694}, {\"ngram\": \"female\", \"from\": 3711, \"to\": 3717}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beyond visual examinations, blood tests documenting hormone levels and/or chromosome testing were used.\", \"from\": 3720, \"to\": 3823, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"visual examinations\", \"from\": 3727, \"to\": 3746}, {\"ngram\": \"blood tests\", \"from\": 3748, \"to\": 3759}, {\"ngram\": \"hormone levels\", \"from\": 3772, \"to\": 3786}, {\"ngram\": \"chromosome testing\", \"from\": 3794, \"to\": 3812}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But asresearchhas revealed, the effects of testosterone on performance are often overstated, and understandings of sporting performance and gender require muchmore nuanced approaches.\", \"from\": 3824, \"to\": 4007, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"asresearchhas\", \"from\": 3828, \"to\": 3841}, {\"ngram\": \"the effects\", \"from\": 3852, \"to\": 3863}, {\"ngram\": \"testosterone\", \"from\": 3867, \"to\": 3879}, {\"ngram\": \"performance\", \"from\": 3883, \"to\": 3894}, {\"ngram\": \"understandings\", \"from\": 3921, \"to\": 3935}, {\"ngram\": \"sporting performance\", \"from\": 3939, \"to\": 3959}, {\"ngram\": \"gender\", \"from\": 3964, \"to\": 3970}, {\"ngram\": \"muchmore nuanced approaches\", \"from\": 3979, \"to\": 4006}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aftermany years of critique, the IOC halted such practices in 1999.\", \"from\": 4009, \"to\": 4076, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4042, \"end\": 4045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3098228103452494e-42, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"critique\", \"from\": 4028, \"to\": 4036}, {\"ngram\": \"such practices\", \"from\": 4053, \"to\": 4067}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In place of outdated sex tests that fail to recognise the physiological and socio-psychological complexities of gender identity, the IOC introduced a new set ofguidelinesprioritising the basic human rights of privacy, inclusion and participation.\", \"from\": 4078, \"to\": 4324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4211, \"end\": 4214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3098228103452494e-42, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 4081, \"to\": 4086}, {\"ngram\": \"outdated sex tests\", \"from\": 4090, \"to\": 4108}, {\"ngram\": \"the physiological and socio-psychological complexities\", \"from\": 4132, \"to\": 4186}, {\"ngram\": \"gender identity\", \"from\": 4190, \"to\": 4205}, {\"ngram\": \"a new set\", \"from\": 4226, \"to\": 4235}, {\"ngram\": \"the basic human rights\", \"from\": 4261, \"to\": 4283}, {\"ngram\": \"privacy\", \"from\": 4287, \"to\": 4294}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 4296, \"to\": 4305}, {\"ngram\": \"participation\", \"from\": 4310, \"to\": 4323}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the IOC sets out the framework in the hope of guiding other international organisations towards more inclusive understandings of gender, the guidelines remain contested.\", \"from\": 4326, \"to\": 4501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4336, \"end\": 4339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3098228103452494e-42, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the framework\", \"from\": 4349, \"to\": 4362}, {\"ngram\": \"the hope\", \"from\": 4366, \"to\": 4374}, {\"ngram\": \"other international organisations\", \"from\": 4386, \"to\": 4419}, {\"ngram\": \"more inclusive understandings\", \"from\": 4428, \"to\": 4457}, {\"ngram\": \"gender\", \"from\": 4461, \"to\": 4467}, {\"ngram\": \"the guidelines\", \"from\": 4469, \"to\": 4483}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some organisations opted to take alternative approaches to testing and proving an athlete's \\\"true\\\" gender identity - for example,World Athleticscontinue to use testosterone testing.\", \"from\": 4503, \"to\": 4684, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some organisations\", \"from\": 4503, \"to\": 4521}, {\"ngram\": \"alternative approaches\", \"from\": 4536, \"to\": 4558}, {\"ngram\": \"testing\", \"from\": 4562, \"to\": 4569}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete's \\\"true\\\" gender identity\", \"from\": 4582, \"to\": 4617}, {\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 4624, \"to\": 4631}, {\"ngram\": \"testosterone testing\", \"from\": 4663, \"to\": 4683}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:A win for transgender athletes and athletes with sex variations: the Olympics shifts away from testosterone tests and toward human rights The boxing events at the Paris Olympics are not being organised by the IBA, but instead by a special IOC-appointed unit.\", \"from\": 4686, \"to\": 4955, \"entities\"